description: From Ancient Greek τόκος (tókos, “childbirth, gestation; offspring”) + γένεσις (génesis, “origin, source”)  +‎ -ic.

adjectives.description: tocogenetic (comparative more tocogenetic, superlative most tocogenetic)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) Pertaining to the evolutionary process in which the higher terms are generated by the lower through creative synthesis.
